com.github.davidmoten.rtree

Class RTree<R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.davidmoten.rtree.RTree<R>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - the entry type

    public final class RTree<R>
extends Object
    Immutable in-memory 2D R-Tree with configurable splitter heuristic.

      • delete

        public RTree<R> delete(R value,
              Geometry geometry)
        Delete one entry comprised of the given value and Geometry. This method has no effect if the entry is not present. The entry must match on both value and geometry to be deleted.
        Parameters:
        value - the value of the Entry to be deleted
        geometry - the geometry of the Entry to be deleted
        Returns:
        a new immutable R-tree without one instance of the specified entry

      • delete

        public RTree<R> delete(Entry<R> entry)
        Delete one entry if it exists. If multiple copies of the entry are in the R-tree only one will be deleted. The entry must match on both value and geometry to be deleted.
        Parameters:
        entry - the Entry to be deleted
        Returns:
        a new immutable R-tree without one instance of the specified entry

      • search

        public rx.Observable<Entry<R>> search(rx.functions.Func1<? super Geometry,Boolean> condition)

        Returns an Observable sequence of Entry that satisfy the given condition. Note that this method is well-behaved only if:

        condition(g) is true for Geometry g implies condition(r) is true for the minimum bounding rectangles of the ancestor nodes

        distance(g) < sD is an example of such a condition.

        Parameters:
        condition - return Entries whose geometry satisfies the given condition
        Returns:
        sequence of matching entries

      • ascendingDistance

        public static final <S> Comparator<Entry<S>> ascendingDistance(Rectangle r)

        Returns a comparator that can be used to sort entries returned by search methods. For example:

        search(100).toSortedList(ascendingDistance(r))

        Type Parameters:
        S - the entry type
        Parameters:
        r - rectangle to measure distance to
        Returns:
        a comparator to sort by ascending distance from the rectangle
